milestones.description: Chris Gayle and Sehwag's 27-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 18 between Sehwag and Sangakkara
Chris Gayle and Sangakkara's 98-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 49 between Ricky Ponting and Gilchrist
Rahul Dravid and Flintoff's 63-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 22 between Chris Cairns and Fleming
Rahul Dravid and Pietersen's 15-run partnership is ICC's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 6 between Hayden and Fleming
Shaun Pollock has broken the record for most ODIs (2) as captain for ICC, going past Ricky Ponting
Sangakkara has become the top scorer for ICC in ODIs with 125 runs, going past Ricky Ponting's 115
Brian Lara has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (3) for ICC, going past Vettori
Sangakkara has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for ICC breaking Chris Cairns's record
This is the highest match aggregate (601) involving teams Australia & ICC World XI in ODIs

stories.title: Gilchrist lays Ashes ghost to rest
stories.subTitle: Australia v World XI, 2nd ODI, Melbourne
stories.summary: Adam Gilchrist's batting has regained its freedom after an English summer of claustrophobia caused by Andrew Flintoff. With Flintoff watching and suffering, Gilchrist smashed Australia's fastest one-day century from 73 balls
